Maritzburg United have announced Fadlu Davids as their new head coach at a press conference currently underway in Pietermaritzburg.Davids impressed greatly as Premier Soccer League team Maritzburg s caretaker-coach in two stints in the past season.He enjoyed a significantly higher win ratio than United s other two coaches in the campaign Ernst Middendorp and Roger de SA and guided the KwaZulu-Natal team to only their second top eight place in seventh.Their previous highest finish was eighth under current Kaizer Chiefs coach Steve Komphela in 2014-15.Davids was a striker for Silver Stars and Maritzburg.His goals as the First Division's top scorer in 2007-08 helped the Team of Choice gain promotion back to the PSL as NFD champions having been relegated the previous season. - TimesLIVE